education.description:
Wisq is building the world's first AI HR generalist to transform the enterprise HR operating model.

Personally leading outbound demand generation, running coordinated plays with marketing and executing signal-based outreach.

Q1 '25: 120%, Q2 '25: 187% quota attainment.

AI-powered platform to help students find classes, professors, and more. Aggregated reviews, built a recommendation engine, and built a course catalog.

1,500+ users // 4,000+ courses searched at UW-Madison.

Venture shut down in May 2025 due to lack of commercial viability.

Led development efforts for building an FSA claim automation tool. Set up infrastructure to securely handle PHI, strung together AI technologies (vision models, fine-tuned BERT model for text classification, proprietary data synthesis), and led team to build frontend prototype for pilot partner.

Venture shut down in Nov 2024.

Built automated due diligence questionaire bot augmented on historical company data.

Deployed IT-related projects to [AWS Lambda](https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/)/Linux. [Snowflake](https://www.snowflake.com/en/) data lake integrity with SQL queries.

Customer discovery interviews in the healthcare claims submission space.

Performing technology commercialization evaluation and go-to-market strategy on new innovation.

Leveraging generative AI to explore solutions in the legal budgeting and administrative operations space.

API endpoints, ETL framework, data synthesis with [Claude Haiku](https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-3-haiku).

Built full-stack MVP web application with recommendation engine powered by [Cohere Rerank 3](https://cohere.com/blog/rerank-3)

Built academic advisor tool for UW-Madison undergraduates using LLMs and Retrieval Augmented Generation.

Led full-stack web development for product MVP, technology commericalization evaluation, go-to-market strategy, and promotion efforts.

Explored SEO methods like guest blogging, content creation, and more.

Competitor SEO analysis using Regex, Pandas, and Visualization packages in Python.

Sales development representative for Cybersecurity services.

Learned Angular web development framework, used git, specialized in AG-Grid JavaScript concepts.

Integrated AG-Grid tables and functionality onto customer-facing Data Integration and Migration Hub.

Influencer acquisition campaign.

Gathered and edited content for multiple brands, designed mockups, and negotiated with manufacturers.

Performed market research through polling relevant industry professionals.

Wrote user manual for R2 platform.

Simulated test data and graphical analyses using R and Excel.

Learned the importance of positive first impressions on customers.

Practiced prioritization and improvisation skills to adapt to changing restaurant conditions.

Attended to customers needs while keeping the restaurant clean.

Increased overall restaurant efficiency through delegating appropriate tasks to coworkers.

Traveled to Puno, Cusco, Machu Picchu, Lima in Peru; La Paz, the Amazon jungle, and the Galapagos Islands in Ecuador.

Hiked portion of the Incan trail, explored capital cities, performed service work (home restoration, youth education), and was immersed in local language and culture.

Led all marketing efforts via email, text campaigns, and cold-calling to recruit 80+ participants.

Created website, online payment system, custom t-shirts and volleyballs for each participant.

Managed a team of 5 employees/coaches throughout 9 camps over 4 weeks.
Innovation and Entrepreneurship Living and Learning Community.

Moved SEO ranking into the top 3 for relevant keywords by creating backlinks and blog posts.

Generated 4 new revenue streams through construction documentation in the Denver area.

Captured, edited, and produced 21 construction site videos leveraging drones to showcase developments.

First honors all eight semesters.

2-time [Kairos](https://www.muhs.edu/faith-service/retreats) retreat leader. Active member of [Jesuit Honor Society](https://www.muhs.edu/academics/jesuit-honor-society), tutoring students weekly.

Weekly volunteering for after-school program at [Highland Community School](https://www.highlandcommunityschool.org/) in Milwaukee.
Improved 23 paid clients testing results an average of 3 points.
Assistant coach, managing drills and participant safety.

project.description: Turned a competitive hobby into a full-stack web app. So far, logged over 4,000 holes from 50+ active users! Hosted tournament sponsored by Northwestern Mutual.

project.title: Summer Volleyball Camps
project.description: Designed custom t-shirts & volleyballs, recruited 82 participants, and hired 4 coaches. Five successful week-long camps at Bradford Beach, MKE, WI.

project.title: Aerial Photography
project.description: During my 2020 year in Denver, I enjoyed capturing shots of developing suburbs and construction sites using drones and cessna aircraft.

project.title: Comida Andes
project.description: During my semester in Peru, fundraised and kickstarted local chef Johan's online presence.

project.title: EDEM Valencia, Spain
project.description: Participated in a 2-week entrepreneurial pitch competition completely immersed in Spanish language.
